@startuml fig-udp-broadcast-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title UDP broadcast communication (IPv4)

participant "Sender\nSO_BROADCAST=1" as S #FFE0B2
participant "Network\n255.255.255.255:5007" as N #E3F2FD
participant "Receiver A\nbind 0.0.0.0:5007" as RA #C8E6C9
participant "Receiver B\nbind 0.0.0.0:5007" as RB #C8E6C9
participant "Receiver C\nbind 0.0.0.0:5007" as RC #C8E6C9

S -[#1565C0]> N : sendto("Hello #0",\n255.255.255.255:5007)
N -[#43A047]-> RA : datagram delivered
N -[#43A047]-> RB : datagram delivered
N -[#43A047]-> RC : datagram delivered

|||

S -[#1565C0]> N : sendto("Hello #1",\n255.255.255.255:5007)
N -[#43A047]-> RA : datagram delivered
N -[#43A047]-> RB : datagram delivered
N -[#43A047]-> RC : datagram delivered

note over S
  Sender sets SO_BROADCAST
  socket option before sending.
end note

note over RA, RC
  All processes bound to port 5007
  receive every broadcast datagram.
end note

legend right
  Broadcast sends to all hosts on the
  local network segment (L2 domain).
  Destination: 255.255.255.255 or
  the subnet broadcast (e.g. 192.168.1.255).
  Routers do not forward broadcasts.
  Every listening process receives the data.
endlegend
@enduml
